import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import statsmodels.api as sm
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    normal_temps = data['normal']
    n, bins, patches = plt.hist(normal_temps, bins='auto', edgecolor='black')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title("What is the distribution of normal temperatures?", wrap=True)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```

```python
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import statsmodels.api as sm
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    data['day'] = pd.to_datetime(data['day'], errors='ignore')
    data['record'] = pd.to_datetime(data['record'], errors='ignore')
    data['forecast'] = pd.to_datetime(data['forecast'], errors='ignore')
    
    plt.hist(data['normal'], alpha=0.5, label='Normal Temperatures', color='blue')
    plt.hist(data['actual'], alpha=0.5, label='Actual Temperatures', color='red')
    
    plt.xlabel('Temperature')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('How does the distribution of actual temperatures compare to normal temperatures?', wrap=True)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import matplotlib.dates as mdates

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['day'] = pd.to_datetime(data['day'], errors='ignore')
    data['actual'] = pd.to_numeric(data['actual'], errors='coerce')
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.plot(data['day'], data['actual'])
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_formatter(mdates.DateFormatter('%Y-%m-%d'))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('Actual Temperature')
    plt.title('What is the trend of actual temperatures over time?', wrap=True)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['day'] = pd.to_datetime(data['day'], errors='ignore')
    data['record'] = pd.to_datetime(data['record'], errors='ignore')
    
    day_counts = data['day'].value_counts()
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.bar(day_counts.index, day_counts.values)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title("What is the distribution of weather records by day?", wrap=True)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
